==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nonconducting
<hw>Non`con*duct"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Not
conducting; nonconductive; not transmitting a fluid or force; -- used
especially of electric current; <as>thus, in electricity, wax is a
<ex>nonconducting</ex> substance</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nonconduction</ent>⟦br⟧
